  "designDecisions": [
    "Using a singleton in-memory store module (src/lib/store.ts) with pre-seeded demo data so the app is immediately usable without sign-up",
    "Session auth via a signed cookie storing userId; the store holds a mock user roster so login works with hardcoded demo credentials (alice@demo.com / password, bob@demo.com / password, etc.)",
    "Drag-and-drop implemented with native HTML5 drag events via a custom useDragAndDrop hook, avoiding any external DnD library to keep zero-install constraint",
    "Board polling every 3 seconds via setInterval in the board page simulates real-time collaboration between browser tabs without WebSockets",
    "In-memory store is structured as plain TypeScript maps keyed by entity ID so lookups are O(1) and mutations are straightforward",
    "All modal state is managed locally in page/component state using useState; no global state library needed at this scale",
    "Tailwind utility classes used directly throughout; a small cn() helper in src/lib/utils.ts handles conditional class merging without shadcn dependency",
    "Three demo projects with pre-populated boards, columns, tasks, and comments are seeded on first import of the store so reviewers see a rich UI immediately",
    "Priority levels (low/medium/high/urgent) and status are handled as string literals with a color-mapping utility in utils.ts, displayed as colored Badge components",
    "Notifications are generated automatically in the API route handlers when tasks are created/assigned, stored in the in-memory store, and surfaced via the notification panel in the navbar",
    "Task filtering (by assignee, priority, search text) is implemented client-side on the fetched task list for simplicity, avoiding complex server-side query building",
    "Column WIP limits are stored on each column; the KanbanColumn component shows a warning indicator when the task count meets or exceeds the limit",
    "The board page uses a boardId URL param; projects have one board each in the MVP (1-to-1) to keep the data model simple while the schema supports multiple boards per project",
